        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
            "name": "The Shriram Millennium School Sector - 64 - Sector 64"
          },
          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "Abhipriya Mishra"
          },
          "datePublished": "2024-04-13",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "1",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "I had a very bad experience with my son. He was admitted to Shri Ram in class Nursery and that was a fantastic year. As soon as he went to KG, his stress levels increased. The class teacher was rude and kept complaining about each child as if she talking about a 12th grade student. She used to shout at the kids so much. There were many issues like kids coming home with poop stains as they were not cleaned in the washroom. My son's anxiety became so much that he used to cry every morning before going to school and finally we have to opt out from the school. It's not worth paying them so much money for nothing.\n\nWe had a long discussion with the principal as well but no use as the class teacher was school's administrator as well. We were not the only parents, many of us went to meet the principal. During admission they'll tell you that we have 2:1 ratio and only 20 kids in a class, even the sections are divided as per age group but nothing is true. They admitted 28 kids with 6 year old in a section where all the kids were 4.5 years old.\n\nTo mention they don't work on kids writing skill and my son didn't even learnt how to write alphabets till mid session of KG. Finally he went to St. Xaviers New Gurgaon and picked up so well.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
